Class ThroughputLimitQueue<M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • java.util.concurrent.LinkedBlockingQueue<M>
          • com.yahoo.documentapi.ThroughputLimitQueue<M>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<M>, Collection<M>, BlockingQueue<M>, Queue<M>

    public class ThroughputLimitQueue<M>
extends LinkedBlockingQueue<M>
    Queue that limits it's size based on the throughput. Allows the queue to keep a certain number of seconds of processing in its queue.
    See Also:
